    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paste-resist dyeing technique for textiles associated with Japanese folk art tradition. The resist is a rice-flour paste usually applied through a stencil to create a pattern or design. The dye is absorbed anywhere that the resist is not applied.</Note_Text>
